WEBVTT

1
00:00:03.090 --> 00:00:04.197
Previously onTracker...
You collect rewards. right?

2
00:00:04.221 --> 00:00:05.396
A mercenary?

3
00:00:05.527 --> 00:00:06.765
No. I prefer the term
"rewardist." actually.

4
00:00:06.789 --> 00:00:07.789
Is that a term?

5
00:00:07.833 --> 00:00:09.313
My childhood was. um

6
00:00:09.444 --> 00:00:11.402
unusual.

7
00:00:11.533 --> 00:00:13.970
Both my parents were
professors at Berkeley.

8
00:00:14.101 --> 00:00:16.146
till there was this
incident with my dad.

9
00:00:16.277 --> 00:00:18.801
So he took us to
live off the grid.

10
00:00:18.931 --> 00:00:20.759
One
night my mom was out...

11
00:00:20.890 --> 00:00:22.041
We have to go now.
They're coming.

12
00:00:22.065 --> 00:00:23.458
We can't go without Mom.

13
00:00:23.588 --> 00:00:26.026
You never contradict me!

14
00:00:26.156 --> 00:00:27.897
Hey. get off her.

15
00:00:28.028 --> 00:00:30.639
Dad. wait. Dad!

16
00:00:30.769 --> 00:00:33.642
No. No!

17
00:00:33.772 --> 00:00:35.687
Russell. what did you do?!

18
00:00:37.211 --> 00:00:38.864
Russell called.

19
00:00:38.995 --> 00:00:40.320
You spoke
with your brother?

20
00:00:40.344 --> 00:00:41.171
Mom. if there's
something that you know

21
00:00:41.302 --> 00:00:43.826
about Russell or Dad
that I should know.

22
00:00:43.956 --> 00:00:45.045
I need you to tell me.

23
00:00:45.175 --> 00:00:48.744
Block that number. Ignore him.

24
00:02:04.124 --> 00:02:06.343
Hey. Mom. I came
as fast as I could.

25
00:02:07.692 --> 00:02:08.954
Show me.

26
00:02:16.745 --> 00:02:17.745
You didn't see anybody?

27
00:02:17.833 --> 00:02:19.791
No.

28
00:02:23.491 --> 00:02:27.059
Why would someone break
into Dad's office?

29
00:02:27.190 --> 00:02:28.583
I don't know.

30
00:02:28.713 --> 00:02:29.932
Anything missing?

31
00:02:30.062 --> 00:02:31.673
No. not that I can tell.

32
00:02:33.065 --> 00:02:34.850
I overreacted.

33
00:02:34.980 --> 00:02:36.678
I shouldn't have called you.

34
00:02:36.808 --> 00:02:38.984
Sheriff said there'd been
break-ins in the area.

35
00:02:39.115 --> 00:02:40.377
Probably just kids.

36
00:02:43.031 --> 00:02:45.730
Dad always had a place
for everything. didn't he?

37
00:02:48.385 --> 00:02:50.344
Well. that's one
way of putting it.

38
00:02:57.089 --> 00:02:59.788
First time I beat
him to the top.

39
00:02:59.918 --> 00:03:01.181
You were so proud.

40
00:03:01.311 --> 00:03:03.705
I was positive
that he let me win.

41
00:03:03.835 --> 00:03:05.446
Used to drive me crazy.

42
00:03:11.147 --> 00:03:12.147
You should get cameras.

43
00:03:12.192 --> 00:03:14.585
And be spied on? No. thank you.

44
00:03:17.675 --> 00:03:19.286
No need for it. really.

45
00:03:19.416 --> 00:03:20.852
I'm sorry I bothered you.

46
00:03:20.983 --> 00:03:22.811
No problem.

47
00:03:22.941 --> 00:03:24.508
I'm glad I was nearby.

48
00:03:28.208 --> 00:03:29.818
Aren't you gonna take that?

49
00:03:29.948 --> 00:03:32.212
It's probably just work.

50
00:03:32.341 --> 00:03:34.605
Teddi. Take it.

51
00:03:34.736 --> 00:03:36.564
Hey. Teddi.

52
00:03:36.694 --> 00:03:38.368
How do you feel about a
nice drive to Montana?

53
00:03:38.392 --> 00:03:39.741
Montana?

54
00:03:39.871 --> 00:03:41.395
Go.

55
00:03:41.525 --> 00:03:44.093
Yeah. Yeah. Why don't I
call you tomorrow morning

56
00:03:44.224 --> 00:03:47.879
and get the details. Thanks.

57
00:03:48.010 --> 00:03:50.665
I'm fine. You can go now.

58
00:03:50.795 --> 00:03:52.715
No. I think I'd feel better
if I spent the night.

59
00:04:04.592 --> 00:04:06.463
So. 35.000 is offered
for information

60
00:04:06.594 --> 00:04:08.552
as to the whereabouts
of Jackson Cheong.

61
00:04:08.683 --> 00:04:10.424
age 27.

62
00:04:10.554 --> 00:04:13.078
Works as an accountant
in Missoula. Montana.

63
00:04:13.209 --> 00:04:16.125
The reward was posted by
his parents. Mark and Eden.

64
00:04:27.354 --> 00:04:29.027
Is this a recent photo
of your son Jackson?

65
00:04:29.051 --> 00:04:30.139
About a year ago.

66
00:04:30.270 --> 00:04:32.141
He was volunteering
at the library.

67
00:04:32.272 --> 00:04:33.272
Free tax advice.

68
00:04:33.360 --> 00:04:35.666
Jackson was a bit shy.

69
00:04:35.797 --> 00:04:38.321
so it was good for him to
get out and meet people.

70
00:04:38.452 --> 00:04:39.844
You say he met a woman?

71
00:04:39.975 --> 00:04:40.976
Rebecca Smith.

72
00:04:41.106 --> 00:04:42.369
How long ago was that?

73
00:04:42.499 --> 00:04:43.892
About two months ago.

74
00:04:44.022 --> 00:04:45.372
There a photo of her?

75
00:04:50.986 --> 00:04:52.335
You can say it.

76
00:04:52.466 --> 00:04:54.381
She's too old for him.

77
00:04:54.511 --> 00:04:56.470
20 years. at least.

78
00:04:56.600 --> 00:04:59.734
Your son's 27 years
old. he's an adult.

79
00:04:59.864 --> 00:05:01.451
If you're looking for
someone to tell him

80
00:05:01.475 --> 00:05:02.582
who he can and cannot
fall in love with.

81
00:05:02.606 --> 00:05:04.260
I'm not your guy. It's not that.

82
00:05:04.391 --> 00:05:05.391
He's missing.

83
00:05:05.435 --> 00:05:08.264
Quit his job. cancelled
his cell phones.

84
00:05:08.395 --> 00:05:09.787
left his apartment.

85
00:05:09.918 --> 00:05:11.876
and emptied his bank accounts.

86
00:05:12.007 --> 00:05:14.202
You think something happened
to him? Hopefully it's nothing.

87
00:05:14.226 --> 00:05:15.402
and we're just overreacting.

88
00:05:15.532 --> 00:05:18.013
He's our only child.

89
00:05:18.143 --> 00:05:20.363
We tried to track down
Rebecca Smith ourselves.

90
00:05:20.494 --> 00:05:22.365
but there's nothing online.

91
00:05:22.496 --> 00:05:24.541
We can't even figure
out where she works.

92
00:05:24.672 --> 00:05:26.040
What makes you so sure
he's with her now?

93
00:05:26.064 --> 00:05:28.086
Well. he was with her the
last time we spoke to him.

94
00:05:28.110 --> 00:05:31.635
I don't know how to say it.
he's taken with her. I guess.

95
00:05:31.766 --> 00:05:34.203
The moment Jackson met
that woman. he changed.

96
00:05:34.334 --> 00:05:36.074
Stopped returning our calls.

97
00:05:36.205 --> 00:05:37.467
missing family dinners.

98
00:05:37.598 --> 00:05:40.078
And his accounting firm
called looking for him

99
00:05:40.209 --> 00:05:42.733
after he missed a few
clients' meetings.

100
00:05:42.864 --> 00:05:46.650
And then two weeks later. he
quit his job and vanished.

101
00:05:46.781 --> 00:05:48.304
Anything else you can recall?

102
00:05:48.435 --> 00:05:50.872
Last time we saw
him. he looked tired.

103
00:05:51.002 --> 00:05:53.614
Like he's been up for days.

104
00:05:53.744 --> 00:05:56.051
He said he was doing
some work for Rebecca.

105
00:05:56.181 --> 00:05:57.966
When I asked him what
it was. he said it was

106
00:05:58.096 --> 00:05:59.881
the kind that people
can't find out about.

107
00:06:00.011 --> 00:06:02.013
that he could get
in trouble for.

108
00:06:02.144 --> 00:06:03.580
Any idea what that might be?

109
00:06:03.711 --> 00:06:05.669
I'm thinking this Rebecca
has him cooking books

110
00:06:05.800 --> 00:06:08.716
or laundering money.
He wasn't himself.

111
00:06:08.846 --> 00:06:10.718
Something bad has
happened to him.

112
00:06:10.848 --> 00:06:13.547
I just know it.

113
00:06:19.640 --> 00:06:20.858
Bobby.

114
00:06:20.989 --> 00:06:23.295
Rebecca Smith? Smith?
Are you kidding me?

115
00:06:23.426 --> 00:06:24.862
There's. like. a
million results.

116
00:06:24.993 --> 00:06:26.081
Oh. good. you got my text.

117
00:06:26.211 --> 00:06:27.343
You're lucky I speak Colter.

118
00:06:27.474 --> 00:06:28.625
Most people wouldn't
know what to do

119
00:06:28.649 --> 00:06:29.824
with a random photo.

120
00:06:29.954 --> 00:06:32.174
zero context. next to one
of the most common names

121
00:06:32.304 --> 00:06:33.697
in North America.

122
00:06:33.828 --> 00:06:35.327
Is this the part where you
tell me how hard it was.

123
00:06:35.351 --> 00:06:36.791
but somehow you
managed to find her?

124
00:06:36.874 --> 00:06:39.399
Pretty much. but I
don't have her yet.

125
00:06:39.529 --> 00:06:40.680
How long do you think
it's gonna take you

126
00:06:40.704 --> 00:06:42.116
to sift through all
that? No time at all.

127
00:06:42.140 --> 00:06:44.229
There's an app for
that. Built it myself.

128
00:06:44.360 --> 00:06:46.101
Of course you did.

129
00:06:46.231 --> 00:06:48.364
Okay. good news and bad news.

130
00:06:48.495 --> 00:06:50.148
No matches for the
facial recognition

131
00:06:50.279 --> 00:06:52.455
overlap with the name.

132
00:06:52.586 --> 00:06:55.545
but I do have a mug shot
for a Rebecca Pendergast.

133
00:06:55.676 --> 00:06:57.242
who's looking real same-same.

134
00:06:57.373 --> 00:06:58.808
Same like identical?

135
00:06:58.940 --> 00:06:59.940
See for yourself.

136
00:07:05.250 --> 00:07:06.948
Yeah. that's her.

137
00:07:07.078 --> 00:07:08.340
So she's using a fake name.

138
00:07:08.471 --> 00:07:10.299
Mug shot.

139
00:07:10.430 --> 00:07:11.430
What was she in for?

140
00:07:11.518 --> 00:07:13.607
Insurance fraud. wire fraud.

141
00:07:13.737 --> 00:07:15.347
plus some tax evasion.

142
00:07:15.478 --> 00:07:16.890
Looks like she hasn't
served any time. though.

143
00:07:16.914 --> 00:07:17.785
The charges were dropped.

144
00:07:17.915 --> 00:07:18.915
Jackson's parents said

145
00:07:19.003 --> 00:07:20.523
all of his bank
accounts were drained.

146
00:07:20.570 --> 00:07:22.635
Sounds like she's a con
woman and he's the next mark.

147
00:07:22.659 --> 00:07:23.854
You said insurance
fraud. Any chance...

148
00:07:23.878 --> 00:07:25.619
Great minds.

149
00:07:30.319 --> 00:07:31.625
Yep.

150
00:07:31.755 --> 00:07:33.801
Cross-reference
with Jackson Cheong.

151
00:07:33.931 --> 00:07:35.672
There's our girl. Ooh.

152
00:07:35.803 --> 00:07:37.761
She's the beneficiary
of a big ol'

153
00:07:37.892 --> 00:07:39.676
fat policy Jackson took out.

154
00:07:39.807 --> 00:07:41.983
That application have
an address on it?

155
00:08:43.347 --> 00:08:44.698
Let me go!

156
00:08:44.828 --> 00:08:46.351
You said you'd let
me leave. Please!

157
00:08:46.482 --> 00:08:48.440
You can't make me stay here.

158
00:08:51.095 --> 00:08:53.620
Make it stop! She's
trying to kill me!

159
00:08:53.750 --> 00:08:56.318
She wants me dead! WOMAN:
I want you to sit down.

160
00:08:56.448 --> 00:08:57.841
No! I don't want to.

161
00:08:57.972 --> 00:09:01.192
That's fine. But I have
to ask you to stop yelling.

162
00:09:01.323 --> 00:09:03.064
You can't make me!

163
00:09:03.194 --> 00:09:05.370
What the hell?

164
00:09:07.372 --> 00:09:09.592
How do you know?

165
00:09:09.723 --> 00:09:11.376
You don't know
anything about me.

166
00:09:13.074 --> 00:09:17.208
Why is this happening
to me? It's not fair!

167
00:09:18.427 --> 00:09:20.560
You can't make me.
How do you know?

168
00:09:20.690 --> 00:09:23.780
You don't know
anything about me.

169
00:09:50.372 --> 00:09:51.460
Who the hell are you?

170
00:09:51.591 --> 00:09:53.549
Yeah. sorry. I
kicked the door in.

171
00:09:53.680 --> 00:09:55.595
It's a bit of a
misunderstanding.

172
00:09:55.725 --> 00:09:57.050
It's actually a funny story
if you care to hear it.

173
00:09:57.074 --> 00:09:58.075
Guess not.

174
00:10:16.790 --> 00:10:18.400
Let's try this again.

175
00:10:18.530 --> 00:10:20.141
Who the hell are you?

176
00:10:20.271 --> 00:10:21.751
Colter Shaw.

177
00:10:21.882 --> 00:10:23.274
Let me see some I.D.

178
00:10:23.405 --> 00:10:24.754
Pocket.

179
00:10:28.105 --> 00:10:30.025
Like I said. man. I don't
want any trouble. okay?

180
00:10:30.151 --> 00:10:31.674
I'm not here to steal things.

181
00:10:31.805 --> 00:10:33.260
I'm here on a job.
just like you guys.

182
00:10:34.459 --> 00:10:35.939
What job is that?

183
00:10:36.070 --> 00:10:37.811
I'm looking for Jackson Cheong.

184
00:10:40.509 --> 00:10:41.509
Never heard of him.

185
00:10:41.553 --> 00:10:43.207
This is private property.

186
00:10:43.338 --> 00:10:44.707
We can call the cops
and have you arrested

187
00:10:44.731 --> 00:10:45.775
for breaking and entering.

188
00:10:45.906 --> 00:10:47.255
Or maybe I shoot you.

189
00:10:47.385 --> 00:10:49.083
Tell them I was
standing my ground.

190
00:10:49.213 --> 00:10:50.974
If you were gonna shoot me.
you would've done it already.

191
00:10:50.998 --> 00:10:52.869
Same goes for calling the cops.

192
00:10:54.741 --> 00:10:56.901
I'm just gonna go. all right?
I don't want any trouble.

193
00:11:01.704 --> 00:11:03.837
Better not see you here again.

194
00:11:03.967 --> 00:11:04.968
Yeah.

195
00:11:08.015 --> 00:11:09.415
I got a bad feeling
about this one.

196
00:11:09.494 --> 00:11:11.018
What are you talking about?

197
00:11:11.148 --> 00:11:12.715
Rebecca Pendergast.

198
00:11:12.846 --> 00:11:14.258
She's got a really
impressive surveillance setup

199
00:11:14.282 --> 00:11:15.979
at her house. private security.

200
00:11:16.110 --> 00:11:18.286
Whatever Jackson Cheong's
got himself involved in.

201
00:11:18.416 --> 00:11:19.698
it's much worse
than a bad romance.

202
00:11:19.722 --> 00:11:21.042
You're
thinking blackmail?

203
00:11:21.158 --> 00:11:23.204
Some kind of kidnapping ring?

204
00:11:23.334 --> 00:11:24.334
I don't know yet.

205
00:11:27.948 --> 00:11:29.708
I'm gonna find out what
the hell is going on.

206
00:12:01.764 --> 00:12:05.072
You've arrived here in a
moment of potential transformation.

207
00:12:05.202 --> 00:12:06.682
It's there.

208
00:12:06.813 --> 00:12:10.642
The part of you that
is ready to change.

209
00:12:10.773 --> 00:12:13.863
Put aside all those negative
thoughts standing in your way.

210
00:12:13.994 --> 00:12:16.779
All those walls you
let others put up.

211
00:12:16.910 --> 00:12:21.001
walls so high they block the
light that shines for us all.

212
00:12:23.873 --> 00:12:25.113
Are you ready to see the light?

213
00:12:25.179 --> 00:12:27.224
We're ready.

214
00:12:27.355 --> 00:12:29.836
One man can lead you to it.

215
00:12:29.966 --> 00:12:31.228
Seth.

216
00:12:41.456 --> 00:12:42.674
Close your eyes.

217
00:12:44.067 --> 00:12:46.504
We must see the light
before we can feel it.

218
00:12:46.635 --> 00:12:48.506
We see it.

219
00:12:48.637 --> 00:12:50.421
It's here for you.

220
00:12:50.552 --> 00:12:52.293
It's all around us.

221
00:12:52.423 --> 00:12:55.470
Waiting to be tapped by
those who are willing

222
00:12:55.600 --> 00:12:57.037
to put in the work.

223
00:13:07.047 --> 00:13:08.222
You. sir.

224
00:13:08.352 --> 00:13:10.050
I see you.

225
00:13:11.442 --> 00:13:13.314
I see what you're carrying.

226
00:13:13.444 --> 00:13:15.272
The pain.

227
00:13:15.403 --> 00:13:17.231
Like a stone.

228
00:13:19.320 --> 00:13:21.278
Colter. is it?

229
00:13:21.409 --> 00:13:23.150
Colter Shaw.

230
00:13:25.065 --> 00:13:27.763
We have much to discuss.

231
00:13:27.894 --> 00:13:29.591
I look forward to
our time together.

232
00:13:33.682 --> 00:13:35.075
And you. ma'am.

233
00:13:36.337 --> 00:13:38.034
I see your loss.

234
00:13:39.514 --> 00:13:41.821
I see the grief that
you're trying to hide.

235
00:14:02.929 --> 00:14:06.584
So. it's... it's a cult?

236
00:14:06.715 --> 00:14:08.935
Well. I don't think they'd
use that word. but yes.

237
00:14:09.065 --> 00:14:10.501
They're offering empowerment.

238
00:14:10.632 --> 00:14:11.938
A path to becoming alpha.

239
00:14:12.068 --> 00:14:13.940
It's not uncommon for
organizations like this

240
00:14:14.070 --> 00:14:15.855
to isolate people
from their loved ones.

241
00:14:15.985 --> 00:14:17.920
They-they find an emotional
wedge. they drive it in.

242
00:14:17.944 --> 00:14:19.467
and once they do that

243
00:14:19.597 --> 00:14:20.816
they've got total control.

244
00:14:20.947 --> 00:14:22.122
Can you get him out?

245
00:14:22.252 --> 00:14:24.864
Aside from forcibly
removing him.

246
00:14:24.994 --> 00:14:26.102
if Jackson doesn't
want to leave.

247
00:14:26.126 --> 00:14:27.431
there's really nothing I can do.

248
00:14:27.562 --> 00:14:29.042
All we're asking
is that you try.

249
00:14:30.260 --> 00:14:31.479
You don't strike me as a man

250
00:14:31.609 --> 00:14:32.828
to give up so easily.

251
00:14:34.221 --> 00:14:35.439
No. sir. I'm not.

252
00:14:52.500 --> 00:14:53.980
Hey. Hey.
guys. I need to know

253
00:14:54.067 --> 00:14:55.347
all the information you can find

254
00:14:55.459 --> 00:14:57.548
about an organization
called Positive Light.

255
00:14:57.679 --> 00:14:59.855
They got a headquarters about
an hour outside Missoula.

256
00:14:59.986 --> 00:15:01.267
I'm headed there first
thing tomorrow morning.

257
00:15:01.291 --> 00:15:02.703
I need to know what
I'm walking into.

258
00:15:02.727 --> 00:15:04.947
We'll get into it. I'll
be moving fast. They know

259
00:15:05.078 --> 00:15:06.998
I'm looking for Jackson.
They'll be ready for me.

260
00:15:44.682 --> 00:15:46.206
Do you think we can
do that tomorrow?

261
00:15:46.336 --> 00:15:47.511
Yes.

262
00:15:47.642 --> 00:15:49.470
Thank you. You can go.

263
00:15:49.600 --> 00:15:51.211
Where's Jackson Cheong?

264
00:15:51.341 --> 00:15:52.952
Mr. Shaw.

265
00:15:53.082 --> 00:15:55.476
I had a feeling we'd
be seeing you again.

266
00:15:55.606 --> 00:15:57.130
Where is he?

267
00:15:57.260 --> 00:15:59.262
There's no need for
the tough guy pose.

268
00:15:59.393 --> 00:16:01.961
Jackson's not being kept
here against his will.

269
00:16:02.091 --> 00:16:04.137
Then he can tell
me that himself.

270
00:16:05.138 --> 00:16:06.574
Colter.

271
00:16:06.704 --> 00:16:08.141
May I call you Colter?

272
00:16:09.577 --> 00:16:11.057
Jackson's happy here.

273
00:16:11.187 --> 00:16:13.581
He's found his place with us.

274
00:16:13.711 --> 00:16:16.758
And we've really come to depend
on his financial guidance.

275
00:16:16.888 --> 00:16:18.281
Great.

276
00:16:19.543 --> 00:16:20.805
Where is he?

277
00:16:20.936 --> 00:16:23.678
Unfortunately. he's in
a session with Seth.

278
00:16:25.071 --> 00:16:26.898
I figured he might be.

279
00:16:27.029 --> 00:16:29.031
Perhaps you'd like to meet Seth.

280
00:16:29.162 --> 00:16:31.468
I'd really like to see Jackson.

281
00:16:32.992 --> 00:16:35.124
I'm afraid that's not
going to be possible.

282
00:16:35.255 --> 00:16:36.952
Unless you meet with Seth first.

283
00:16:42.827 --> 00:16:44.438
Okay.

284
00:16:50.313 --> 00:16:52.359
Are you ready?

285
00:16:54.839 --> 00:16:57.755
Seth. this is Colter Shaw.

286
00:16:57.886 --> 00:16:59.235
Mr. Shaw.

287
00:17:02.978 --> 00:17:04.414
It's good to see you again.

288
00:17:05.675 --> 00:17:07.548
I'm here to see Jackson Cheong.

289
00:17:07.678 --> 00:17:09.506
Rebecca explained.

290
00:17:10.855 --> 00:17:12.135
But I can't allow that to happen

291
00:17:12.204 --> 00:17:14.424
until we've had
a chance to talk.

292
00:17:14.555 --> 00:17:15.991
take your measure.

293
00:17:16.122 --> 00:17:17.775
I'm not sure what
we'd talk about.

294
00:17:17.906 --> 00:17:20.430
Well. why don't we
start with something simple?

295
00:17:20.560 --> 00:17:22.693
Tell me about yourself.

296
00:17:22.824 --> 00:17:23.954
I like piÃ±a coladas.

297
00:17:24.086 --> 00:17:26.262
And getting caught in the rain.

298
00:17:26.393 --> 00:17:28.917
Mr. Shaw. I'd prefer if we
didn't waste each other's time.

299
00:17:29.048 --> 00:17:31.006
We already know a lot about you.

300
00:17:31.137 --> 00:17:32.834
who you work with.
all sorts of things.

301
00:17:32.964 --> 00:17:35.750
So you got a peek at my I.D.
and you did some googling?

302
00:17:37.012 --> 00:17:39.145
I won't be
intimidated like that.

303
00:17:39.275 --> 00:17:41.973
I'm not trying to
intimidate you.

304
00:17:42.104 --> 00:17:43.845
I'm not a violent man.

305
00:17:43.975 --> 00:17:46.804
There are all types of violence.

306
00:17:46.935 --> 00:17:49.111
I suppose that's true.

307
00:17:49.242 --> 00:17:52.245
Tell me

308
00:17:52.375 --> 00:17:54.247
what sort of man
was your father?

309
00:17:57.641 --> 00:17:59.774
I'm not here to talk about that.

310
00:17:59.904 --> 00:18:01.819
It's okay to talk
about the past.

311
00:18:01.950 --> 00:18:04.039
It's part of what we do here.

312
00:18:04.170 --> 00:18:06.041
You blackmail your members
with their secrets.

313
00:18:06.172 --> 00:18:07.390
Truth.

314
00:18:08.826 --> 00:18:10.045
We did look you up.

315
00:18:10.176 --> 00:18:11.699
Your family. too.

316
00:18:11.829 --> 00:18:14.528
Can't be too careful these days.

317
00:18:14.658 --> 00:18:16.138
And information. well.

318
00:18:16.269 --> 00:18:17.792
it's there if you
know where to look.

319
00:18:21.883 --> 00:18:23.058
Your father.

320
00:18:24.015 --> 00:18:26.279
Quite an impressive man.

321
00:18:27.280 --> 00:18:28.672
A scientist.

322
00:18:28.803 --> 00:18:30.239
Then activist.

323
00:18:31.632 --> 00:18:33.024
Then he fell.

324
00:18:34.200 --> 00:18:35.810
Cliff near your
family homestead.

325
00:18:35.940 --> 00:18:37.159
if I'm not mistaken.

326
00:18:37.290 --> 00:18:38.421
An accident.

327
00:18:40.075 --> 00:18:42.121
At least that's what
the newspaper said.

328
00:18:43.687 --> 00:18:46.081
But your eyes tell me
something different.

329
00:18:47.474 --> 00:18:48.997
Maybe he jumped?

330
00:18:50.520 --> 00:18:51.869
Or was pushed?

331
00:18:53.393 --> 00:18:55.046
Is the not knowing the source

332
00:18:55.177 --> 00:18:57.223
of all that pain
you're carrying?

333
00:18:59.399 --> 00:19:02.271
Tell me how he came to be fired
from his job as professor.

334
00:19:04.012 --> 00:19:05.318
Google didn't tell you that?

335
00:19:06.623 --> 00:19:07.885
No.

336
00:19:09.148 --> 00:19:11.411
Oh. you don't know why. do you?

337
00:19:13.326 --> 00:19:15.545
So your mother keeps
secrets from you?

338
00:19:16.807 --> 00:19:18.287
Interesting.

339
00:19:20.550 --> 00:19:22.030
I'd like to see Jackson.

340
00:19:22.161 --> 00:19:23.684
Tell me one truth
about your father

341
00:19:23.814 --> 00:19:25.425
and I will let you see Jackson.

342
00:19:25.555 --> 00:19:27.601
It's that simple.

343
00:19:27.731 --> 00:19:29.864
He made me the man that I am.

344
00:19:29.994 --> 00:19:31.735
But it wasn't easy. was it?

345
00:19:31.866 --> 00:19:33.266
Growing up with a
father like that.

346
00:19:33.302 --> 00:19:34.825
He prepared me for
people like you.

347
00:19:34.956 --> 00:19:36.194
people that like to play games.

348
00:19:36.218 --> 00:19:37.326
Your father liked to play games?

349
00:19:37.350 --> 00:19:40.004
Tell me what sort of
games he liked to play.

350
00:19:40.135 --> 00:19:41.832
My father didn't play games.

351
00:19:41.963 --> 00:19:43.660
All was life or death with him.

352
00:19:43.791 --> 00:19:45.880
Preparing you to live
in this world. perhaps.

353
00:19:46.010 --> 00:19:47.403
Perhaps.

354
00:19:48.883 --> 00:19:51.190
I'm sorry you had
to endure that.

355
00:19:52.713 --> 00:19:54.236
But thank you

356
00:19:54.367 --> 00:19:55.890
for opening up to me.

357
00:19:56.020 --> 00:19:58.022
I know that wasn't easy.

358
00:19:58.153 --> 00:19:59.937
But it shows me

359
00:20:00.068 --> 00:20:02.940
that you might be someone
I can grow to trust.

360
00:20:03.071 --> 00:20:04.681
I don't think so.

361
00:20:09.817 --> 00:20:12.217
You bring that thing near me.
I'll shove it down your throat.

362
00:20:16.476 --> 00:20:18.739
You get a burn when
you witness and hold

363
00:20:18.869 --> 00:20:20.610
another person's secrets.

364
00:20:30.446 --> 00:20:33.275
It is an honor to share
one of yours. Colter Shaw.

365
00:20:37.410 --> 00:20:39.716
Jackson will be waiting
for you in the garden.

366
00:20:52.163 --> 00:20:53.948
Are you sure this
is a good idea?

367
00:20:54.078 --> 00:20:56.342
Jackson's one of ours.

368
00:20:58.039 --> 00:21:00.259
Let Mr. Shaw talk to
him and he'll see.

369
00:21:00.389 --> 00:21:02.173
And if he does cause trouble?

370
00:21:02.304 --> 00:21:04.350
Mr. Shaw has a very
dangerous profession.

371
00:21:07.004 --> 00:21:08.528
Accidents happen.

372
00:21:18.407 --> 00:21:19.732
Yeah. You in
a good place to talk?

373
00:21:19.756 --> 00:21:21.116
Not really. You
talk. I'll listen.

374
00:21:21.236 --> 00:21:22.933
Is that not how we do it?

375
00:21:23.064 --> 00:21:24.064
I'm serious. Bobby.

376
00:21:24.108 --> 00:21:25.390
We got to be
careful on this one.

377
00:21:25.414 --> 00:21:27.373
Copy that. I always am.

378
00:21:27.503 --> 00:21:28.983
So. yeah. Teddi
and Velma called.

379
00:21:29.113 --> 00:21:30.724
gave me the scoop.

380
00:21:30.854 --> 00:21:31.899
Positive Light... Mm-hmm.

381
00:21:32.029 --> 00:21:33.422
Super weird.

382
00:21:33.553 --> 00:21:35.250
There's nothing negative
about them online.

383
00:21:35.381 --> 00:21:37.339
No articles. no
message boards...

384
00:21:37.470 --> 00:21:38.688
Nada. man.

385
00:21:38.819 --> 00:21:39.819
Doesn't seem right.

386
00:21:39.907 --> 00:21:40.951
Yeah. hell no. it ain't.

387
00:21:41.082 --> 00:21:42.953
Started digging in the archives.

388
00:21:43.084 --> 00:21:44.390
mostly dead links.

389
00:21:44.520 --> 00:21:46.455
Stuff that's been completely
wiped from the Internet.

390
00:21:46.479 --> 00:21:48.611
And I found a bunch of lawsuits.

391
00:21:48.742 --> 00:21:50.589
mostly civil cases that
have either been settled

392
00:21:50.613 --> 00:21:53.094
or abruptly dropped.
Like Rebecca's charges.

393
00:21:53.224 --> 00:21:54.313
Mm-hmm.

394
00:21:54.443 --> 00:21:56.140
Bunch of the cases
called for a...

395
00:21:56.271 --> 00:21:58.360
David Grassley as a witness.

396
00:21:58.491 --> 00:22:00.057
He and his wife Jana
were both members.

397
00:22:00.188 --> 00:22:01.581
It looks like David

398
00:22:01.711 --> 00:22:04.105
prepared all of Positive
Light's financial statements.

399
00:22:04.235 --> 00:22:06.194
And he was a signer
on all their accounts.

400
00:22:06.325 --> 00:22:07.645
You got an address for me? Well

401
00:22:07.674 --> 00:22:09.110
that's the thing.

402
00:22:09.240 --> 00:22:10.677
David Grassley's dead.

403
00:22:10.807 --> 00:22:12.548
When? How?

404
00:22:12.679 --> 00:22:13.549
Hit-and-run.

405
00:22:13.680 --> 00:22:15.812
Cops never found the driver.

406
00:22:15.943 --> 00:22:17.423
Looks like the wife
made a big stink

407
00:22:17.553 --> 00:22:19.990
about how the cops were all
botching the investigation

408
00:22:20.121 --> 00:22:21.862
on purpose. but
she's gone quiet.

409
00:22:21.992 --> 00:22:23.907
Packed up and moved
to Southern Wyoming.

410
00:22:24.038 --> 00:22:25.431
She's afraid to talk.

411
00:22:25.561 --> 00:22:26.886
We need to send someone
there in person.

412
00:22:26.910 --> 00:22:28.129
Make her feel comfortable.

413
00:22:28.259 --> 00:22:29.696
Where exactly in Wyoming?

414
00:22:29.826 --> 00:22:31.151
Cheyenne. That's less than
two hours from Denver.

415
00:22:31.175 --> 00:22:32.438
Do you mind. uh...?

416
00:22:32.568 --> 00:22:34.875
Talk to Velma and
Teddi? I'm on it.

417
00:22:40.097 --> 00:22:41.403
Jackson.

418
00:22:41.534 --> 00:22:43.231
I'm Colter Shaw.

419
00:22:43.362 --> 00:22:44.802
Some place we could
talk in private?

420
00:22:45.538 --> 00:22:46.843
I'm on gardening duty.

421
00:22:48.454 --> 00:22:50.673
But if you want to
talk. you can help me.

422
00:22:57.158 --> 00:22:58.420
I'm not coming home.

423
00:22:58.551 --> 00:23:00.814
My parents should
know that by now.

424
00:23:00.944 --> 00:23:02.250
Your parents didn't even know

425
00:23:02.381 --> 00:23:03.532
where you were until last night.

426
00:23:03.556 --> 00:23:06.167
You can tell them I'm fine.

427
00:23:06.297 --> 00:23:08.430
I'm better than fine. I'm happy.

428
00:23:08.561 --> 00:23:10.161
Great. Why don't you
tell them yourself?

429
00:23:11.302 --> 00:23:13.609
Seth says I'm at a very

430
00:23:13.740 --> 00:23:15.742
delicate stage of
my development.

431
00:23:17.047 --> 00:23:18.614
I don't think
that's a good idea.

432
00:23:27.580 --> 00:23:29.538
When the soil is hard like that.

433
00:23:29.669 --> 00:23:31.584
you just start
shallow. all right?

434
00:23:33.107 --> 00:23:35.414
And then. you can always go
deeper on your second pass.

435
00:23:35.544 --> 00:23:37.285
Makes sense?

436
00:23:37.416 --> 00:23:39.200
You're a gardener. too? Kind of.

437
00:23:39.330 --> 00:23:40.810
My dad taught me.

438
00:23:40.941 --> 00:23:43.378
Believed in self-sufficiency.

439
00:23:43.509 --> 00:23:44.949
You had to be able
to feed yourself.

440
00:23:45.075 --> 00:23:47.513
Growing your own
food is part of that.

441
00:23:47.643 --> 00:23:49.732
Seth wants us to be
self-sufficient. too.

442
00:23:49.863 --> 00:23:51.734
To know our own strength.

443
00:23:53.736 --> 00:23:55.782
My parents spent their
whole lives hovering.

444
00:23:57.218 --> 00:23:58.524
If it were up to them.

445
00:23:58.654 --> 00:24:00.700
I'd still be sleeping
in my childhood bedroom.

446
00:24:01.875 --> 00:24:03.137
Huh.

447
00:24:04.530 --> 00:24:05.313
What about all these
cameras. though?

448
00:24:05.444 --> 00:24:07.228
I mean. isn't that hovering?

449
00:24:09.056 --> 00:24:12.102
People at my stage need more
support to stay on the path.

450
00:24:12.233 --> 00:24:14.540
You got people who
check on you. right?

451
00:24:14.670 --> 00:24:16.367
Seth tell you that?

452
00:24:16.498 --> 00:24:18.326
Seth trusts me

453
00:24:18.457 --> 00:24:19.806
with important information.

454
00:24:19.936 --> 00:24:21.590
Financial information.
Is that right?

455
00:24:21.721 --> 00:24:23.121
I'm not just some
numbers cruncher.

456
00:24:24.550 --> 00:24:27.770
Seth makes me feel like I can
do anything I put my mind to.

457
00:24:27.901 --> 00:24:29.821
Does that include walking
out the door right now?

458
00:24:31.295 --> 00:24:32.688
I'm not gonna do that.

459
00:24:36.605 --> 00:24:38.520
Why don't you.
uh. give it a try?

460
00:24:40.914 --> 00:24:42.568
Shallow. then
deep. There you go.

461
00:24:42.698 --> 00:24:43.873
A little bit easier?

462
00:24:46.049 --> 00:24:47.573
Your dad knew what he was doing.

463
00:24:47.703 --> 00:24:50.097
He knew his way around the
outdoors. that's for sure.

464
00:24:52.229 --> 00:24:53.535
He could be very charming.

465
00:24:53.666 --> 00:24:55.102
Lot of charisma.

466
00:24:57.147 --> 00:24:59.106
I remember. uh

467
00:24:59.236 --> 00:25:00.673
as a kid when he
would look at me.

468
00:25:00.803 --> 00:25:02.243
sometimes it felt
like he was just

469
00:25:03.719 --> 00:25:05.460
looking right into me.

470
00:25:08.115 --> 00:25:09.464
Sounds like Seth.

471
00:25:10.421 --> 00:25:11.771
When Seth looks at you.

472
00:25:11.901 --> 00:25:13.599
How does it make you feel?

473
00:25:15.209 --> 00:25:16.689
Like I'm free.

474
00:25:18.429 --> 00:25:20.780
Free of all the things

475
00:25:20.910 --> 00:25:22.129
that held me back.

476
00:25:26.873 --> 00:25:30.006
It sure wasn't like
that with my dad.

477
00:25:30.137 --> 00:25:31.747
He could be mean.

478
00:25:32.748 --> 00:25:34.271
Impossible to please.

479
00:25:35.664 --> 00:25:37.405
I kept trying.

480
00:25:37.536 --> 00:25:39.407
I tried until the day he died.

481
00:25:40.930 --> 00:25:42.453
That sound familiar?

482
00:25:43.411 --> 00:25:45.848
Is Seth ever mean. Jackson?

483
00:25:45.979 --> 00:25:47.763
How about Rebecca?
Is she ever mean?

484
00:25:51.680 --> 00:25:53.856
They only want
what's best for me.

485
00:26:05.041 --> 00:26:06.434
Yeah. well...

486
00:26:06.565 --> 00:26:09.176
Listen. I got to go.

487
00:26:09.306 --> 00:26:10.306
My number. okay?

488
00:26:12.005 --> 00:26:13.572
Give me a call.

489
00:26:13.702 --> 00:26:15.102
Reach out if you
ever want to talk.

490
00:26:17.271 --> 00:26:18.794
You stay or go.

491
00:26:18.925 --> 00:26:20.840
You decide what's best for you.

492
00:26:22.189 --> 00:26:23.364
Why do you care?

493
00:26:25.409 --> 00:26:26.846
You don't even know me.

494
00:26:27.803 --> 00:26:28.891
I don't know you.

495
00:26:30.284 --> 00:26:32.199
I used to be you.

496
00:26:37.726 --> 00:26:39.510
All right. Nice
chatting with you.

497
00:26:39.641 --> 00:26:41.251
Good luck.

498
00:26:41.382 --> 00:26:44.080
When can we make time for
another session. Mr. Shaw?

499
00:26:44.211 --> 00:26:45.604
We're just getting started.Yeah.

500
00:26:45.734 --> 00:26:46.909
I'll see myself out.

501
00:27:53.323 --> 00:27:55.238
I know why you're here. Colter.

502
00:27:55.369 --> 00:27:57.327
Where's Jackson?

503
00:27:57.458 --> 00:27:59.939
He's on a healing retreat.
You won't find him.

504
00:28:04.204 --> 00:28:06.312
You kidnapped him because he
reached out to me? - No.

505
00:28:06.336 --> 00:28:07.947
He went voluntarily.

506
00:28:08.077 --> 00:28:10.514
He gave me your number
voluntarily. too.

507
00:28:10.645 --> 00:28:12.212
I'm the one who texted you.

508
00:28:12.342 --> 00:28:13.517
I know it's hard to believe

509
00:28:13.648 --> 00:28:15.215
because you're
naturally suspicious.

510
00:28:15.345 --> 00:28:16.999
But I don't blame you.

511
00:28:17.130 --> 00:28:19.828
Who wouldn't be after
your difficult childhood?

512
00:28:19.959 --> 00:28:22.831
You live on the road
trying to run away from it.

513
00:28:22.962 --> 00:28:25.007
But you can never really
leave it all behind.

514
00:28:25.138 --> 00:28:26.443
can you. Colter?

515
00:28:28.315 --> 00:28:29.359
Where'd you take him?

516
00:28:30.665 --> 00:28:33.494
I won't let you
pull him back down.

517
00:28:33.624 --> 00:28:36.453
But the door to a new life
is always open to you.

518
00:28:36.584 --> 00:28:40.283
But should you choose
a different path.

519
00:28:40.414 --> 00:28:43.156
please know that we
defend our own. Colter.

520
00:28:43.286 --> 00:28:44.984
We protect them

521
00:28:45.114 --> 00:28:46.812
from the wolves and the darkness

522
00:28:46.942 --> 00:28:49.118
that you're trying to
bring to Jackson's life.

523
00:28:49.249 --> 00:28:50.729
That a threat?

524
00:28:50.859 --> 00:28:52.861
Oh. I think you know
exactly what I mean.

525
00:29:16.624 --> 00:29:18.017
You can go.

526
00:29:21.237 --> 00:29:22.456
But if it were up to me.

527
00:29:22.586 --> 00:29:24.414
you'd be gone permanently.

528
00:29:24.545 --> 00:29:27.069
Well. lucky for me. you're
not in charge. are you?

529
00:29:32.379 --> 00:29:33.510
Do you have Jackson?

530
00:29:33.641 --> 00:29:34.966
They got
wind of our meet.

531
00:29:34.990 --> 00:29:36.533
nabbed him and took
off before I got there.

